  "title": "Senior / Mechanical Design Engineer",
  "description": "<p>Our client is a leading provider of integrated automation solutions to the semiconductor industries worldwide. The Company primarily designs, develops and distributes a wide range of automated equipment that caters to the front and back-end processes of IC assembly. They are currently hiring for a Mechanical Design Engineer and will like to invite interested canddiate to send your detailed resume to talent@asiasearch.com.sg</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Senior / Mechanical Design Engineer</strong></u></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Description &amp; Requirements</strong></p>\n<p>Design and develop series of marking/inspection/ sorting/customised semiconductor equipment to meet the processing and automation needs of customers. Main duties involve:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Design standardization</li>\n  <li>Costing and project management</li>\n  <li>Machine and module conceptualization design</li>\n  <li>Design for manufacturing (DFM), design for assembly (DFA) and Concurrent engineering</li>\n  <li>Pneumatic / hydraulic circuit design</li>\n  <li>Detail fabrication drawings, assembly drawings and layout drawings</li>\n  <li>Selection and sizing of standard components available off the shelf</li>\n  <li>Undertake new product development or be involved in sustaining engineering/CIPs</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>EDUCATION AND EXPERIENCE</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor/ Master of Mechanical Engineering</li>\n  <li>3D solid Modeling, preferably Pro-E (others like Solid Edge, Auto Inventor, Mechanical Desktop, Solid Designer are also acceptable).</li>\n  <li>Strong project management skills</li>\n  <li>Good track record in:</li>\n</ul>\n<ol>\n  <li>Ultra High Precision machine design</li>\n  <li>High Speed Pick and Place mechanism design</li>\n  <li>Structural, kinematics and dynamic analysis and FEA simulation</li>\n  <li>Geometrical tolerance and dimensional analysis (e.g. stack up error)</li>\n  <li>Engineering material selection</li>\n  <li>Design troubleshooting</li>\n  <li>Application of analysis tools like FMEA, DOE</li>\n</ol>",
